This sets `a` to the value of `i` if `i` is smaller or equal `a` and sets `smallestVal` to the value of `a` if `i` is greater than `a`. In the case that `i` is never greater than `a` after `a` got updated `smalledtVal` will not be updated to the smallest value. I&#39;d suggest getting rid of `smallestVal` and just returning `a` as `a` should always contain the smallest value. That being said `a` should probably be named `smallestVal` as it&#39;s a more descriptive name.

